ECPM - Equal-Cost Multi-Path
-------
Transit Gateway is a centralized hub connecting multiple VPCs and on-prem networks. ECMP distributes traffic across multiple equal-cost VPN tunnels simultaneously for higher throughput вҖ” each tunnel gives 1.25 Gbps so 4 tunnels give 5 Gbps total. ECMP requires BGP dynamic routing and must be enabled on Transit Gateway

No! VPN is not used for single VPC вҖ” it's used to connect outside networks to AWS.
-------------------
VPN use cases:
------------------
VPN is used to connect:

On-premise office вҶ’ AWS VPC вң…
Your laptop (remote work) вҶ’ AWS VPC вң…
Another cloud (Azure/GCP) вҶ’ AWS VPC вң…
Data center вҶ’ AWS VPC вң…

NOT used:
Within single VPC вқҢ
Between subnets in same VPC вқҢ

When you need VPN:

+-----------------------------+------------------------------+
| Scenario                    | Solution                     |
+-----------------------------+------------------------------+
| Office вҶ’ AWS                | Site-to-Site VPN             |
| Remote developer вҶ’ AWS      | Client VPN                   |
| Multiple VPCs               | Transit Gateway (not VPN)    |
| On-prem вҶ’ multiple VPCs     | TGW + VPN                    |
+-----------------------------+------------------------------+

ECMP:

Without ECMP:
  VPN Tunnel 1 вҶ’ active (1.25 Gbps)
  VPN Tunnel 2 вҶ’ standby вқҢ
  Only one tunnel used вқҢ

With ECMP:
  VPN Tunnel 1 вҶ’ active (1.25 Gbps) вң…
  VPN Tunnel 2 вҶ’ active (1.25 Gbps) вң…
  VPN Tunnel 3 вҶ’ active (1.25 Gbps) вң…
  VPN Tunnel 4 вҶ’ active (1.25 Gbps) вң…
  Total = 5 Gbps вң…
  All tunnels used simultaneously вң…
