Types of VPC Endpoints?

Two types вҖ” Interface Endpoint and Gateway Endpoint.

1. Gateway Endpoint:

VPC
 в””в”Җв”Җ Route Table вҶ’ Gateway Endpoint вҶ’ S3 / DynamoDB

Detail
--------------------------------------------------------
Services supported : S3 and DynamoDB only
How it works       : Added to route table
Cost               : вң… Free
Private IP         : вқҢ No вҖ” uses route table entry

2. Interface Endpoint (AWS PrivateLink):

VPC
 в””в”Җв”Җ Subnet вҶ’ ENI (private IP) вҶ’ Interface Endpoint вҶ’ AWS Service

| Detail               | Description                                              |
|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| Services supported   | Almost all AWS services (ECR, SSM, CloudWatch, STS etc.) |
| How it works         | Creates ENI in your subnet                               |
| Cost                 | вқҢ Paid вҖ” $0.01/hr per AZ                                |
| Private IP           | вң… Yes вҖ” gets private IP in your subnet                  |

Comparison:

| Feature            | Gateway Endpoint       | Interface Endpoint     |
|--------------------|------------------------|------------------------|
| Services           | S3, DynamoDB only      | 100+ AWS services      |
| Cost               | Free                   | Paid                   |
| Route table change | вң… Yes                 | вқҢ No                  |
| ENI created        | вқҢ No                  | вң… Yes                 |
| DNS resolution     | вқҢ No                  | вң… Yes                 |

Your EKS context:

EKS nodes in private subnet:
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ S3 access        вҶ’ Gateway Endpoint (free) вң…
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ DynamoDB access  вҶ’ Gateway Endpoint (free) вң…
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ ECR pull         вҶ’ Interface Endpoint (paid) вң…
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ CloudWatch logs  вҶ’ Interface Endpoint (paid) вң…
 в””в”Җв”Җ SSM access       вҶ’ Interface Endpoint (paid) вң…

One-liner: 
Gateway Endpoint = free, only S3/DynamoDB, uses route table. 
Interface Endpoint = paid, supports 100+ AWS services, creates ENI with private IP in your subnet.

