ENI = Elastic Network Interface вҖ” a virtual network card attached to an EC2 instance or service.

Simple analogy:

Physical server вҶ’ has a physical NIC (network card)
AWS EC2/Service вҶ’ has an ENI (virtual network card)

What ENI has:

ENI
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ Private IP address
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ Public IP (optional)
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ MAC address
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ Security Groups
 в””в”Җв”Җ Source/Dest check flag

Where ENI is used:

| Use case                | How                              |
|--------------------------|----------------------------------|
| EC2 instance             | Every EC2 gets one ENI by default |
| Interface VPC Endpoint   | ENI created in your subnet       |
| RDS                      | ENI created in your subnet       |
| Lambda in VPC            | ENI created for Lambda           |
| EKS nodes                | Each node has ENI                |
| NLB                      | ENI per AZ                       |

com.amazonaws.ap-south-1.ecr.dkr   вҶ’ image pull
com.amazonaws.ap-south-1.ecr.api   вҶ’ ECR API calls

One-liner: 
VPC Endpoints created in VPC Console вҶ’ Endpoints вҶ’ Create Endpoint вҖ” Gateway needs only route table selection, 
Interface needs subnet + security group + enable private DNS.

Which subnet is required for VPC Endpoint?

Gateway Endpoint вҖ” no subnet needed:

Gateway Endpoint
 в””в”Җв”Җ attaches to Route Table only (not subnet)
      в””в”Җв”Җ any subnet using that route table gets access automatically

| Detail            | Value           |
|-------------------|-----------------|
| Subnet required   | вқҢ No           |
| What you select   | Route table     |
| Works for         | S3, DynamoDB    |

Interface Endpoint вҖ” private subnet required:

Interface Endpoint
 в””в”Җв”Җ ENI created inside вҶ’ Private Subnet вң…
      в””в”Җв”Җ private IP assigned from that subnet range

| Detail            | Value                                      |
|-------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| Subnet required   | вң… Yes вҖ” private subnet                    |
| Why private       | Traffic should never go to internet        |
| What you select   | Private subnet + security group            |
| Works for         | ECR, CloudWatch, SSM, STS etc.             |

Why not public subnet for Interface Endpoint:

Public subnet вҶ’ has IGW route вҶ’ traffic could go internet вқҢ
Private subnet вҶ’ no IGW route вҶ’ traffic stays inside VPC вң…

Your EKS context:

EKS nodes in private subnet
        в”Ӯ
Interface Endpoint ENI also in private subnet
        в”Ӯ
EKS node вҶ’ ENI (same subnet) вҶ’ AWS Service
Traffic never leaves VPC вң…

One-liner: 
Gateway Endpoint needs no subnet вҖ” just route table. 
Interface Endpoint must be placed in private subnet so ENI gets a private IP and traffic never reaches the internet.
